subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen.
Male abdominal tergites yellowish brown, sternites obscure yellow. Segments with dark brown submarginal ring, posterior margin of both tergites and sternites narrowly grayish, only first sternite entirely yellow. Female abdomen pale yellow. Male terminalia (
Fig. 9
) obscure yellow. Ninth tergite transverse, posterior margin slightly concave. Gonocoxite (
Fig. 8
) elongate, longer than gonostyli. Outer gonostylus glabrous, blackened, slightly arched, point-apexed with small spine at middle. Inner gonostylus setiferous, long and narrow, nearly parallel-sided. Interbase (
Fig. 10
) long and slender, slightly arched and sinuous. Paramere (
Fig. 11
) V-shaped, ventral part widened. Aedeagus (
Fig. 12
) directed ventrally with a single wide opening. Ovipositor (
Fig. 13
) yellow with brown cercus and hypovalva. Tenth tergite strongly elongate, cercus long, narrow, distal part turned upwards, point- apexed. Hypovalva straight, getting narrower distally, tip pale, reaching to about middle of cercus. Spermatheca small, rounded.
